cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on image representation and compression. The introduction of a variance-constrained rate term also suggests that it may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of the Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM) for optimization suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The application of the algorithm in image set compression suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the investigation of inter-image correlations suggests that it may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
